cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM 

This paper deals with semantic segmentation of satellite images, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed framework involves the use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) for unsupervised domain adaptation, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of color mapping for adapting the spectral distribution of images, which could be considered as a topic in graphics (cs.GR) or multimedia (cs.MM).
